Review: smart smart smart. shows the moments you don’t expect of the usual sequences.

maybe I want to like more than I do? i think something that will reward rewatching. lots of history of acting references (tv plays, actors studio Elia Kazan vs Lee Strasberg and all the rest). visually, the usual top.
one of those movies that loomed large in the culture of my childhood, but that I never actually saw. the LA scenes, cringely dated. the action scenes, not as much. efficient storytelling.
wowza. al pacino sometimes I don’t get…but here. in goat mode. it’s like an old Hollywood movie, but 90s.
might it be a truism that the greatest superhero movie of our superhero era was made before it ever even started?
